      "span_text": "Impacts of social stress on susceptibility to AN-like behavior are conveyed during adolescence Social stressors experienced during adolescence have been reported to synergize with genetic factors to influence discrete neurochemical and behavioral deficits observed in some affective disorders. To explore whether early exposure to social isolation stress is critical to elicit abnormal feeding behaviors, we compared the response to CR in adult females in which single housing was initiated at 414 weeks vs 5 weeks."
